⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of Umaro
node FF6 · FF6 · ⟦Umaro:FF6:4257f2⟧

WHO   — Umaro — the wild yeti
WHAT  — A secret recruit of Final Fantasy VI's World of Ruin — the strongest brute in the party, an uncontrollable berserker who cannot be commanded, who acts on his own each turn with raw, devastating force.
WHERE — FF6 · Final Fantasy VI  Framework inputs: Final Fantasy VI (America's Final Fantasy III, 1994)  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because not every ally is a comrade who reasons — some are forces of nature you can only point toward the enemy; because strength without speech is still strength, and the broken world needs every hand, even a clawed one.
HOW   — By sheer berserk power — hurling boulders, smashing foes, and even seizing his own allies to fling them as living weapons — uncommandable, unkillable in spirit, a storm given fur and fang.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  I am no soldier and no friend who speaks — I am the mountain's own beast, and when you loose me, I am the avalanche.

spoken token : thein-rorn-lol   ·   hex : 4257f2
